text:
355 ml bottle bought at CitySuper in New Town Plaza, Shatin;
Clear deep blackish brown colour; Half finger head and beige foam which lasts for 90 seconds; Pretty Good lacing and notable carbonation; Nice fragrant aroma of roasted dark malt, with chocolate, light cream, sweet caramel, vanilla, plums, raisins and nuts; Very light sweet taste of light roasted malt, with dark bread, light chocolate, coffee, strong nuts, cream, very light liquorices, light alcohol, and hint of grass; Med to light body, slick and creamy palate; Taste profile is very nice slightly sweet dark malt taste - reminiscent of a basic Guinness FES - with strong nuttiness complemented by just the right amount of  chocolate, coffee, cream and booze; Hoppiness is very light as expected for the style, yet light grassy taste and zapping astringency make a very soild presence and nice finish. Good!

Comments: This American take of Dunkler Bock is very well made and just right in many aspects: slightly sweet, Dunkel nose is here but inoffensive to me, strong nuttyness, and right amount of chocolate, coffee, creaminess and booziness. Highly enjoyable, and if its taste can be a bit more sweet, it will be perfect. Highly recommended!
